Lecture Notebook 9: Mutualism phase planes

For the final Lecture Notebook, I’d like you to work through the final set of two-species interactions: mutualisms. As discussed in Chapter 10 of your book and in my lecture material, mutaulism had been modeled in a variety of ways to overcome mutualism’s tendency to positively feed back where both populations benefit each other to the point where they grow exponentially with no regulation. As described in class last Tuesday, I’d like for you to model facultative mutualism as (I) a weak, stable interaction and (II) strong, unstable interaction; obligate mutualism as (III) an unstable, weak interaction and (IV) a strong, (unfortunately) unstable interaction; and where one species is facultative and the other obligate, where there is an interior equilibrium when (V) the obligate species is weakly affected by the facultative species and (VI) when the obligate species is strongly affected by the facultative species. Your figures should look similar to what I’ve presented below.

mut <- function(t, y, parameters) {
  with(as.list(c(y, parameters)), {
    N1 <- y[1]
    N2 <- y[2]
    dN1dt <- N1*(r1 - alpha*N1 + beta1*N2)
    dN2dt <- N2*(r2 - alpha*N2 + beta2*N1)
    return(list(c(dN1dt, dN2dt)))
  })
}

fac.weak <- c(r1 = 1, r2 = 1, alpha = 0.5, beta1 = 0.1, beta2 = 0.1)
fac.strong <- c(r1 = 1, r2 = 1, alpha = 0.5, beta1 = 0.75, beta2 = 0.75)
ob.weak <- c(r1 = -1, r2 = -1, alpha = 0.5, beta1 = 0.25, beta2 = 0.25)
ob.strong <- c(r1 = -1, r2 = -1, alpha = 0.5, beta1 = 1, beta2 = 1)
fac.ob.left <- c(r1 = 1, r2 = -0.5, alpha = 0.5, beta1 = 0.1, beta2 = 2/3)
fac.ob.right <- c(r1 = 0.5, r2 = -1.5, alpha = 0.5, beta1 = 0.5, beta2 = 0.85)

XLIM <- c(-1, 5)
YLIM <- c(-1, 5)

par(mfrow = c(3, 2), mar = c(4.5, 4.5, 0.1, 0.1), oma = c(3, 3, 2, 1))
plot(x = NA, xaxs = "i", yaxs = "i", xlim = XLIM, ylim = YLIM, las = 1, xlab = bquote(N[1]), ylab = bquote(N[2]))
trash <- flowField(deriv = mut, parameters = fac.weak, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 20, arrow.head = 0.025)
trash <- nullclines(deriv = mut, parameters = fac.weak, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 200, lwd = 2)
mtext(text = "Weak mutualisms", line = 0.5, outer = F, side = 3)
mtext(text = "Facutative\nmutualisms", line = 4.5, outer = F, side = 2)

plot(x = NA, xaxs = "i", yaxs = "i", xlim = XLIM, ylim = YLIM, las = 1, xlab = bquote(N[1]), ylab = bquote(N[2]))
trash <- flowField(deriv = mut, parameters = fac.strong, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 20)
trash <- nullclines(deriv = mut, parameters = fac.strong, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 200, lwd = 2)
mtext(text = "Strong mutualisms", line = 0.5, outer = F, side = 3)

plot(x = NA, xaxs = "i", yaxs = "i", xlim = XLIM, ylim = YLIM, las = 1, xlab = bquote(N[1]), ylab = bquote(N[2]))
trash <- flowField(deriv = mut, parameters = ob.weak, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 20)
trash <- nullclines(deriv = mut, parameters = ob.weak, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 200, lwd = 2)
mtext(text = "Obligate\nmutualisms", line = 4.5, outer = F, side = 2)

plot(x = NA, xaxs = "i", yaxs = "i", xlim = XLIM, ylim = YLIM, las = 1, xlab = bquote(N[1]), ylab = bquote(N[2]))
trash <- flowField(deriv = mut, parameters = ob.strong, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 20)
trash <- nullclines(deriv = mut, parameters = ob.strong, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 200, lwd = 2)

plot(x = NA, xaxs = "i", yaxs = "i", xlim = XLIM, ylim = YLIM, las = 1, xlab = bquote(N[1]), ylab = bquote(N[2]))
trash <- flowField(deriv = mut, parameters = fac.ob.left, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 20)
trash <- nullclines(deriv = mut, parameters = fac.ob.left, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 200, lwd = 2)
mtext(text = "Facultative-obligate\nmutualisms", line = 4.5, outer = F, side = 2)

plot(x = NA, xaxs = "i", yaxs = "i", xlim = XLIM, ylim = YLIM, las = 1, xlab = bquote(N[1]), ylab = bquote(N[2]))
trash <- flowField(deriv = mut, parameters = fac.ob.right, add = T, x.lim = XLIM, y.lim = YLIM, points = 20)
